{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Building a macOS VM Manager","role":"collectionGroup"},"abstract":[{"text":"Compose the Spooktacular libraries into a first-class Mac app.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article walks through the layered structure of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular SwiftUI app so you can build something comparable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without repeating the architectural decisions we already settled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app target depends on three Swift packages in this repo:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookCore","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — pure Swift domain types. No AppKit, no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization"},{"type":"text","text":", no networking. Use it for models, enums,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and protocol “ports” that describe what the app needs without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"committing to a concrete transport."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookApplication","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — use cases and services that combine"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain types into workflows (RBAC evaluation, tenant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"isolation, runner-pool 